# One Component Per File

Every React component must live in its own file. Never define multiple components in the same file.

```text
# ✅ GOOD
features/search/page/NewSearchPage.tsx       # NewSearchPage
features/search/page/SearchForm.tsx          # SearchForm
features/search/components/SearchCard.tsx    # SearchCard

# ❌ BAD — two components in one file
features/search/page/NewSearchPage.tsx       # NewSearchPage + SearchForm
```

If a component is only used by one parent, it still gets its own file in the same directory. Extract it, give it a co-located CSS file if it has styles, and import it.
